**Describe the bug:**
We have created a button and added a click event for that element. In the click event of the button, we have shown an alert box. When we click on the button element, the click event gets triggered and an alert box gets opened. Once click the ok button on the alert box,  the component OnAfterRender event gets triggered again. Is this is nature of blazor ???

**Version used:**
Microsoft Visual Studio Professional 2019 Preview
Version 16.8.0 Preview 3.0

**To reproduce:**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. Click on the button
2. Alert box gets opened.
3. Now, click on the **ok** button in the alert box.
4. See the onAfterRender gets triggered again

**Expected behavior:**
We thought the OnAfterRender gets triggered only once and does not want to trigger while clicking on the button.

**Actual behavior:**

**Additional context:**

Code Snippet is added below

```razor
@inject IJSRuntime JsRuntime
<div>
    <input type="button" value="Button" @onclick="@Click" />
</div>

@code {

    protected override void OnAfterRender(bool firstRender)
    {
        Console.WriteLine("Hit");
    }

    private async void Click()
    {
        await JsRuntime.InvokeVoidAsync("alert", "Warning!"); // Alert
    }
}
